import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['distance'])
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Distance (miles)')
    ax.axhline(data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['distance'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['distance'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight distances?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('origin')['delay'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)
    ax = data_grouped.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 7), color='orange')
    plt.title('Which airports have the most delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Average Delay (minutes)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Average Delay'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.date

    flight_counts = data['date'].value_counts().sort_index()

    plt.plot(flight_counts.index, flight_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Flight Dates'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
